22:56.933 --> 23:01.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
NII AKUETTEH: Oh, I agree
totally, because also ,on the
global stage, the U.S. looms

23:01.833 --> 23:03.733 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
large.

23:03.733 --> 23:07.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And the U.S. was a
leader in supporting the
independence of South Sudan.

23:09.700 --> 23:13.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But even if you take a more
narrow view of U.S.' own
national interests, it's always

23:16.033 --> 23:18.800 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
been said that ungoverned
spaces breed terrorism,
which eventually can
come to affect the U.S.

23:20.533 --> 23:24.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
So, frankly, when I
look down the road, this
is an American issue.

23:24.600 --> 23:29.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Now, the fighters are
South Sudanese, the
victims are South Sudanese.

23:29.166 --> 23:31.233 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
But it should concern Americans.

23:31.233 --> 23:35.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I think, for one, think
that Congress needs to make
its voice strong and push the

23:35.333 --> 23:40.333 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
State Department to work
with various organizations,
because, otherwise,
it will get worse, and

23:42.300 --> 23:46.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that -- we will then see that
it's beginning to affect the
American interests in ways that

23:46.800 --> 23:48.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
cannot be missed.

23:48.800 --> 23:50.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Brian, as
he points out, the U.S. was
instrumental in trying to birth

23:50.300 --> 23:52.700 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
this nation.

23:52.700 --> 23:55.300 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But is this administration
going to -- are there
any indications that
they're going to

23:55.300 --> 23:57.366 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
pay as close attention to this?

23:57.366 --> 24:01.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
BRIAN ADEBA: Well,
I'm quite optimistic.

24:01.400 --> 24:06.400 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If we look back at the
statements -- the statement
that the U.S. ambassador
to the United Nations,

24:08.366 --> 24:12.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Nikki Haley, uttered a few
weeks ago, it was the very first
time that a member of the Trump

24:14.133 --> 24:17.766 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
administration had come out
very strongly on South Sudan.

24:17.766 --> 24:22.766 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
