counterparts in the Security
Council for inaction on
South Sudan and suggested

24:24.800 --> 24:29.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
that perhaps it's time
now to broach or examine
the possibility of an
arms embargo to stop

24:31.300 --> 24:33.500 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the carnage that is going on.

24:33.500 --> 24:38.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
She also called out
the president of South
Sudan for continuing to
perpetuate the conflict

24:40.300 --> 24:45.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and also the other
political elements
involved in this conflict.

24:45.733 --> 24:49.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
So, that's encouraging.

24:49.166 --> 24:54.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
From a multilateral perspective,
