itself is divided.

25:28.033 --> 25:33.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And within IGAD, what I'm
saying is, the U.S., apart from
pressure like Brian has said, on

25:35.433 --> 25:40.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the Sudanese leaders, South
Sudanese leaders, to also put
pressure on the countries in the

25:40.900 --> 25:42.366 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
region.

25:42.366 --> 25:45.566 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I mean, U.S. relations with
Khartoum is warming up.

25:45.566 --> 25:47.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It has good relations
with Uganda.

25:47.500 --> 25:49.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It has good relations
with Ethiopia.

25:49.033 --> 25:51.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It has good
relations with Kenya.

25:51.066 --> 25:55.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, I, for one, think the U.S.
should also put pressure on
these countries to come to

25:57.500 --> 26:00.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
a meeting of the
minds, because they are
backing different sides.

26:00.200 --> 26:04.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: All
right, Nii Akuetteh, Brian
Adeba, thank you both.

26:04.300 --> 26:09.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
NII AKUETTEH: Thank
you for having us.

26:13.200 --> 26:18.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: More than
eight million Americans suffer
from diabetes, and more than

26:19.633 --> 26:23.633 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
$320 billion are spent every
year treating the disease.

26:23.633 --> 26:27.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But an innovative program
in San Diego is trying to
improve health and reduce those

26:27.266 --> 26:31.266 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
costs by encouraging better
self-management of the disease.

26:31.266 --> 26:34.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Special correspondent
Cat Wise has our report.

26:34.433 --> 26:39.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CAT WISE: Fifty-one year old
Alma Ayala is not a doctor
or a nurse, but she is on the

26:41.766 --> 26:45.766 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
front lines of the diabetes
epidemic in her community.

26:45.766 --> 26:50.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She's a peer educator for a
program called Project Dulce,
which works with people who

26:50.266 --> 26:55.266 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
have diabetes or are at risk of
developing the chronic illness.

26:56.866 --> 26:59.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Her classes are
part informational,
part support group.

26:59.733 --> 27:04.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Ayala says the goal of the
program, which has been held
up as a national model, is for

27:06.133 --> 27:08.500 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
people to feel empowered
about changing their health.

27:08.500 --> 27:12.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That's something she didn't
feel 30 years ago when she
was first diagnosed with the

27:12.900 --> 27:14.100 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
disease.

27:14.100 --> 27:15.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
ALMA AYALA, Project
Dulce: I was devastated.

27:15.500 --> 27:17.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I didn't want to hear
the word diabetes.

27:17.633 --> 27:22.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
I felt that my life was
done, that I was signing
a certificate of death.

27:22.300 --> 27:27.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CAT WISE: Here in San Diego
County, nearly half the adult
population has pre-diabetes

27:28.400 --> 27:30.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
and about 8 percent
have diabetes.

27:30.400 --> 27:35.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's a disease that affects
all socioeconomic groups and
races, but the Latino community

27:35.133 --> 27:37.766 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
has been disproportionately
impacted.

27:37.766 --> 27:41.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And that's the population
Project Dulce has been targeting
for the past 20 years.

27:41.900 --> 27:46.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ALMA AYALA: There are lots
of barriers for the Latino
community, language, insurance.

27:48.333 --> 27:51.466 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Sometimes, doctors don't have
the time to spend with them.

27:51.466 --> 27:56.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So the classes that we provide
is that extra support, working
together with a clinical

27:57.766 --> 27:59.866 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
team to help our
participants stay healthy.

27:59.866 --> 28:04.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
CAT WISE: The program
is scattered throughout
12 clinics in Latino
neighborhoods throughout

28:04.300 --> 28:09.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
San Diego County and was
designed by several local health
care organizations, including

28:09.000 --> 28:11.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
the Scripps Whittier
Diabetes Institute.

28:11.633 --> 28:16.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Dr. Athena Philis-Tsimikas
is an endocrinologist
who oversees the program.

28:16.200 --> 28:18.233 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

28:18.233 --> 28:20.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ATHENA PHILIS-TSIMIKAS, Scripps
Whittier Diabetes Institute:
This is a disease in which you

28:20.400 --> 28:23.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
have to do a number of
management components,
not only every day,
but many times a day.

28:28.033 --> 28:32.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And it's not that easy to expect
someone to remember to test
their blood sugar, take their

28:32.200 --> 28:37.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
pill, to go out and take that
walk, to have exactly the
right meal on the table all the

28:39.133 --> 28:41.233 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
time to take care of this.

28:41.233 --> 28:44.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I don't see any lows there, so
I don't think we have to worry
that you might dip down too

28:44.700 --> 28:46.700 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
low.

28:46.700 --> 28:49.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CAT WISE: To help patients,
a team is set up at each
clinic with a physician, nurse

28:49.666 --> 28:54.666 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
practitioner, a dietitian
and multiple peer
counselors like Ayala who
come from the communities

28:55.833 --> 28:57.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
they serve and also
have the disease.

28:57.533 --> 28:59.633 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

28:59.633 --> 29:02.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ATHENA PHILIS-TSIMIKAS: If you
can train these other people
and professionals to help you

29:02.500 --> 29:07.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
do the other components
that take longer, but
are still absolutely
necessary, then you're

29:07.033 --> 29:11.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
using your team to work very
synergistically to deliver
everything that patient needs in

29:11.466 --> 29:13.133 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
order to improve their care.

29:13.133 --> 29:17.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
CAT WISE: The program
is now adding another
layer, technology.

29:17.033 --> 29:22.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Last year, Tsimikas conducted
a study to see if patients
receiving daily text messages

29:23.200 --> 29:25.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
could manage their
disease even better.

29:25.166 --> 29:28.766 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Artist Gloria Favela-Rocha
was one of the participants.

29:28.766 --> 29:33.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She's a muralist who does large
scale works for hospitals,
schools and private clients.

29:35.733 --> 29:38.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She says, before the study,
she often forgot to regularly
check her glucose levels.

29:39.666 --> 29:41.666 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Project Dulce changed that.

29:41.666 --> 29:43.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GLORIA FAVELA-ROCHA, Diabetes
Patient: The text message would
come every day at the same

29:43.733 --> 29:48.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
time, so if I would lose track
of where I was during my day,
I would hear it ring, and

29:50.066 --> 29:54.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
so I would start checking
my blood sugars, send
in my result right away.

29:54.066 --> 29:59.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It would send me back a
message according to whatever
my result was, like good job,

30:01.000 --> 30:03.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
or maybe you need to
eat something that has a
little more protein today.

30:03.733 --> 30:06.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
So, it was just very --
it was very convenient.

30:06.366 --> 30:11.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CAT WISE: Dr. Tsimikas' team
has also been studying the
effects of continuous glucose

30:11.200 --> 30:16.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
monitoring, which uses Bluetooth
technology to send results
to the patient and physician

30:16.800 --> 30:18.733 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in real time.

30:18.733 --> 30:21.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAGDALENA HERNANDEZ, Diabetes
Patient: This device is
reading my sugar levels.

30:21.033 --> 30:25.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
CAT WISE: Magdalena
Hernandez wears a small
monitor on her stomach.

30:25.433 --> 30:27.566 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MAGDALENA HERNANDEZ: I love it.

30:27.566 --> 30:32.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I love it because I don't have
to prick my finger many times
during the day, and it alerts

30:33.533 --> 30:35.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
me when my blood sugar
goes high or goes low.

30:35.733 --> 30:38.766 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
CAT WISE: And what happens
if your levels go above 200?

30:38.766 --> 30:40.866 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
