41:17.900 --> 41:21.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
This is hypocrisy.

41:21.033 --> 41:24.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And so I think the risk here
is actually to religion.

41:24.933 --> 41:26.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
HARI SREENIVASAN: To
that point, I mean...

41:26.966 --> 41:28.900 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MARK SHIELDS: It's a good point.

41:28.900 --> 41:33.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
On your point, yes, I am deeply
concerned, and have been,
and especially now that we

41:35.966 --> 41:39.966 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
have got a smokescreen
of charitable religious
institutions being formed
basically for political

41:42.000 --> 41:44.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
ends, and for partisan
political purpose.

41:44.800 --> 41:49.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And what it amounts to in public
policy terms is, I'm making
a donation, a tax-deducted

41:52.100 --> 41:57.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
donation, for a political
purpose to support my political
cause or your political cause,

41:58.566 --> 42:00.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
which I think is absolutely
wrong, and it's a corruption.

42:00.833 --> 42:02.633 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MICHAEL GERSON: I just haven't
seen much evidence of it.

42:02.633 --> 42:04.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
HARI SREENIVASAN:
I don't know...

42:04.633 --> 42:08.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARK SHIELDS: We have certainly
seen -- we have seen phony,
bogus charitable foundations

42:08.133 --> 42:10.266 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
created for that purpose.

42:10.266 --> 42:12.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
HARI SREENIVASAN: I
don't socially if this
happens already, but
do you end up picking

42:12.533 --> 42:15.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
your church a little bit
more because you know how
that church is going to vote?

42:15.833 --> 42:19.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I'm going to reveal my Hindu
roots here, but I thought
Jesus was an independent, not a

42:19.666 --> 42:20.900 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Democrat or a Republican.

42:20.900 --> 42:23.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
MICHAEL GERSON: Well,
I think that's true.

42:23.133 --> 42:28.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Whenever a pastor makes a
political statement, they're at
risk of alienating a portion of

42:30.233 --> 42:33.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
their congregation on
issues that have nothing
to do with religion, or
at least their judgment

42:35.366 --> 42:39.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
is not particularly
sanctified on these issues.

42:39.800 --> 42:44.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I mean, I would rather go to the
average bartender for political
advice than the average priest

42:46.733 --> 42:47.733 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
or minister.

42:47.733 --> 42:49.866 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

42:49.866 --> 42:53.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MICHAEL GERSON: So, you know,
I think that they don't have
an expertise in many of these

42:53.033 --> 42:55.200 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
issues.

42:55.200 --> 42:59.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And that's up to laymen
in the church and that,
from the pulpit, there
needs to be fairness.

43:00.700 --> 43:01.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Yes,
all right, Michael
Gerson, Mark Shields.

43:01.966 --> 43:03.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
MARK SHIELDS: It's a
good point you make.

43:03.500 --> 43:04.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
HARI SREENIVASAN:
All right, thank you.

43:04.500 --> 43:05.733 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(CROSSTALK)

43:05.733 --> 43:06.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
HARI SREENIVASAN:
Thank you very much.

43:06.666 --> 43:07.600 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MARK SHIELDS: Thank you, Hari.

43:07.600 --> 43:10.033 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: All right.

43:10.033 --> 43:13.500 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Tomorrow night here in
Washington, the prestigious
PEN/Faulkner Award for
Fiction will be given.

43:15.466 --> 43:18.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Jeffrey Brown talks with the
winning author, the latest in
our "NewsHour" Bookshelf series.

43:18.333 --> 43:23.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: An immigrant
couple from West Africa working
for a wealthy New York family

43:24.500 --> 43:26.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
as the great recession
is about to hit in 2008.

43:26.866 --> 43:31.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The novel "Behold the Dreamers"
is a story of the contemporary
American dream through

43:31.400 --> 43:34.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
the lens of class,
race and immigration.

43:34.200 --> 43:39.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Author Imbolo Mbue came to
the U.S. from Cameroon in 1998
and became a citizen in 2014.

43:41.266 --> 43:42.900 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
This is first nurse novel.

43:42.900 --> 43:45.166 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And because of that, even
more congratulations to you.

43:45.166 --> 43:47.200 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
IMBOLO MBUE, Author, "Behold the
Dreamers": Thank you, Jeffrey.

43:47.200 --> 43:51.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: You're working
here in a great American fiction
tradition about immigration.

43:52.433 --> 43:53.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
What did you want to
bring to that story?

43:53.900 --> 43:55.933 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
What did you want to tell?

43:55.933 --> 43:59.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
IMBOLO MBUE: Well, when I start
writing this novel, it wasn't
very much about immigration.

43:59.666 --> 44:01.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It was about the
financial crisis.

44:01.866 --> 44:06.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I was very interested in how
the financial crisis affected
the lives of New Yorkers from

44:06.566 --> 44:09.166 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
different economic statutes.

44:09.166 --> 44:13.566 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So I wanted to write
about an immigrant from
my country who gets a job
as a chauffeur (INAUDIBLE)

44:13.566 --> 44:18.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
executive, but, of course, an
immigrant coming here for the
American dream and facing the

44:20.533 --> 44:24.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
financial crisis, I wanted to
write about how that affected
him and how -- and also

44:25.966 --> 44:29.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
explore like the dreams
and hopes he has himself
when he came to America.

44:29.533 --> 44:34.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, I ended up writing about
the immigrant experience, coming
here, realizing what America

44:36.500 --> 44:38.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
really is like, and also
deciding whether it is
really worth staying here.

44:38.566 --> 44:42.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: So, these
characters, the main characters,
Jende and Neni, from Cameroon,

44:42.500 --> 44:46.500 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
they're experiencing both
sides of the American dream.

44:46.500 --> 44:51.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They tell us that they see
it as both wonderful and
awful at the same time.

44:51.266 --> 44:53.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
IMBOLO MBUE: Yes.

44:53.266 --> 44:57.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's very complex, this idea
of the American dream, because,
on one hand, when we're back

44:59.133 --> 45:01.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in our countries, we especially,
when I was growing up in
Cameroon, we had this image

45:01.733 --> 45:06.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of American being the sort of
promised land, and this country
where you go to and you work

45:06.466 --> 45:11.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
hard and you get to achieve
this life, a lot of material
success, a house and nice cars

45:11.433 --> 45:12.900 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and (INAUDIBLE) accounts.

45:12.900 --> 45:16.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And that is what they
came for, Jende and Neni.

45:16.033 --> 45:21.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And then they got here, and they
see the realities of social --
a lot of social issues, economic

45:22.366 --> 45:25.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
inequity, and racism and
sexism, and all of those issues.

45:25.933 --> 45:28.000 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And they have to deal with it.

45:28.000 --> 45:31.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And they also have -- see
what it's like for people
who achieve the dream.

45:31.200 --> 45:36.200 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: But by
doing that and by setting
it in that period, you're
also raising question

45:36.200 --> 45:37.200 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of class, right?

45:37.200 --> 45:39.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
IMBOLO MBUE: Right.

45:39.200 --> 45:41.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: But, as a writer,
you have to see this couple
-- you have to see everybody

45:41.700 --> 45:42.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
with some sympathy.

45:42.866 --> 45:43.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
IMBOLO MBUE: Right,
right, right.

45:43.700 --> 45:44.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Right?

45:44.900 --> 45:46.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
So, the Edwards family,
which is wealthy...

45:46.233 --> 45:47.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
IMBOLO MBUE: Right.

45:47.766 --> 45:49.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: ...
and the immigrant
family, they get along.

45:49.833 --> 45:50.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
They don't get along.

45:50.833 --> 45:51.833 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
There are all kinds of clashes.

45:51.833 --> 45:53.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
But for you, what?

45:53.533 --> 45:55.600 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
What are they?

45:55.600 --> 45:58.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
IMBOLO MBUE: Well, for me, it
was, I had a lot of empathy
for the immigrants, because

45:58.100 --> 45:59.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I am an immigrant.

45:59.566 --> 46:02.600 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I am from the same town where
Jende and Neni come from.

46:02.600 --> 46:04.666 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
So I know those struggles.

46:04.666 --> 46:08.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The struggles of the Edwards,
the 1 percent, people who
have that amount of privilege,

46:10.966 --> 46:13.966 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
is not something that I have
dealt with during my life.

46:13.966 --> 46:18.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So I had to push myself to
think about, what are their
struggles, and what does it take

46:18.900 --> 46:20.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
to hold this dream
life together?

46:20.400 --> 46:22.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Because they do
have the dream life.

46:22.100 --> 46:23.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
They have a house
in the Hamptons.

46:23.200 --> 46:25.333 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
They live on the
Upper East Side.

46:25.333 --> 46:28.166 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They have so many privileges.

46:28.166 --> 46:30.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And yet they have
their own struggles.

46:30.166 --> 46:34.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, on one hand, I had one
family that was living the dream
and that family growing after

46:34.066 --> 46:36.033 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the dream.

46:36.033 --> 46:38.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And when the recession
happened, both families had to
deal with the consequences.

46:38.900 --> 46:41.500 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: You referred
to your own background.

46:41.500 --> 46:43.966 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
How much is this your story?

46:43.966 --> 46:48.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
IMBOLO MBUE: In many ways,
you know, I was like Jende and
Neni, in the fact that, when

46:48.133 --> 46:52.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
I came here, I thought
America would be a
sort of promised land.

46:52.766 --> 46:55.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And I do believe that it
is a wonderful country.

46:55.133 --> 46:57.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I think it's a country that
offers a lot of immigrants.

46:57.133 --> 47:01.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But, at the same time, this
American dream, what I have seen
is that it's not accessible,

47:03.766 --> 47:07.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and that somebody like Jende,
a black man without a good
education, and he's also dealing

47:09.800 --> 47:13.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
with not having papers, that
somebody like that, the odds
of moving out of poverty is

47:13.133 --> 47:15.133 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
very difficult.

47:15.133 --> 47:19.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: You're also
dealing in this very difficult
and divisive issue over illegal

47:20.766 --> 47:23.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
immigration, because
they overstay what
they're allowed to.

47:23.033 --> 47:24.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
IMBOLO MBUE: Right,
right, the visa.

47:24.300 --> 47:25.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: They want
to stay in the country.

47:25.333 --> 47:27.000 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They're facing deportation.

47:27.000 --> 47:30.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, you know there's a great
debate in the country over this.

47:30.433 --> 47:32.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
IMBOLO MBUE: Right.

47:32.600 --> 47:36.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: I mean,
you portray them as
sympathetic characters
who want to work hard.

47:37.466 --> 47:38.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
IMBOLO MBUE: Right.

47:38.466 --> 47:40.400 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Right.

47:40.400 --> 47:41.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: But you know
that there are plenty of
people who would say, well, I'm

47:41.600 --> 47:42.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
sorry, you're not
playing by the rules.

47:42.400 --> 47:43.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
IMBOLO MBUE: Right.

47:43.000 --> 47:44.233 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Right.

47:44.233 --> 47:46.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And it is a very,
very complex issue.

47:46.266 --> 47:51.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think that, for me, as a
writer, that my job is to tell
the story and let the reader

47:53.066 --> 47:55.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
decide: Should I empathize with
people like Jende who don't
have papers, or I should vilify

47:55.800 --> 47:57.033 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
them?

47:57.033 --> 48:00.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I don't -- this is not
a moralizing story.

48:00.166 --> 48:05.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think people can read my book
and use it as pro-immigration
or use it as anti-immigration

48:05.733 --> 48:07.166 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
argument.

48:07.166 --> 48:09.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
My place is to tell the story
honestly and completely.

48:09.233 --> 48:13.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
But I think that it is
important to understand
each other's stories.

48:13.066 --> 48:18.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's so easy to put people
in a box and say, oh, people
without any papers, but who are

48:19.266 --> 48:20.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
these people, what
are their stories?

48:20.400 --> 48:21.833 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And I also am a citizen, right?

48:21.833 --> 48:24.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
So, I also understand
the citizen perspective.

48:24.533 --> 48:29.533 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I am an immigrant and
I'm a citizen, and I
know what it's like to
be both and to understand

48:31.533 --> 48:34.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that desire to come here and
work hard, but also that desire
to, like, think about America's

48:34.366 --> 48:36.466 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
future.

48:36.466 --> 48:39.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Let me ask
you finally, as I said,
this is your first novel.

48:39.000 --> 48:41.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And you won a big award.

48:41.033 --> 48:44.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That's got to be a bit of a
surprise, a welcome surprise,
right, for a young writer.

48:44.966 --> 48:45.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
IMBOLO MBUE: Yes.

48:45.966 --> 48:47.400 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Yes, it is a good privilege.

48:47.400 --> 48:49.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I started writing this
book when I was unemployed.

48:49.833 --> 48:52.666 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I had lost my job at the
end of the financial crisis.

48:52.666 --> 48:54.700 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: So, this hit
-- that hit you personally?

48:54.700 --> 48:55.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
IMBOLO MBUE: Yes.

48:55.700 --> 48:56.700 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Yes.

48:56.700 --> 48:59.166 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Yes.

48:59.166 --> 49:01.366 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I thought that writing
a story about people
from my hometown and
other New Yorkers who

49:01.366 --> 49:05.600 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I have met in some ways and
talk about their own struggles.

49:05.600 --> 49:07.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And then I got a novel,
and it got published.

49:07.633 --> 49:11.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And to win an award
like the PEN/Faulkner,
it is a great honor.

49:11.233 --> 49:12.733 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: All right.

49:12.733 --> 49:14.366 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Well, the award-winning book
is "Behold the Dreamers."

49:14.366 --> 49:18.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Imbolo Mbue, thank
you very much.

49:18.500 --> 49:23.500 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
IMBOLO MBUE: Thank you, Jeffrey.

49:25.533 --> 49:28.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
